  "prompt": "The current year is 2014. Why is this the 21st century and not the 20th century?",
  "response": "The current year, 2014, is in the 21st century because centuries are counted starting from year 1 AD. The 1st century included the years 1 to 100, the 2nd century included the years 101 to 200, and so on. Therefore, each century covers a set of years that ends in a number which is one less than a multiple of 100. The 20th century encompassed the years 1901 to 2000, and the 21st century began with the year 2001 and will continue until the year 2100. Thus, 2014 falls within the 21st century.",
